.TH CAT-310DX_RENAME_CLIPS 1 "2026-04-05" "CAT-310DX Tools 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cat-310dx_rename_clips \- rename CAT-310DX LPC/WAV clips using a correlation map
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B python3 cat-310dx_rename_clips.py
[\fB\-\-map\fR \fIFILE\fR]
[\fB\-\-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR]
[\fB\-\-apply\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-wav\fR]
[\fB\-q\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cat-310dx_rename_clips.py
reads a JSON rename map produced by
.BR cat-310dx_correlate.py (1)
and renames \fB.lpc\fR and \fB.wav\fR file pairs in the CAT-310DX clip
directory.
.PP
By default the script runs in
.B dry-run
mode, printing what it would do without making any changes.  Pass
.B \-\-apply
to perform the actual renames.
.PP
The script is idempotent.  If the source file is absent but the destination
already exists, the pair is counted as already done.  If both exist, the pair
is skipped.
.PP
.B Note:
clips extracted with the updated
.B cat-310dx_extract.py
already use sequence-numbered names (e.g. \fB0001_One.lpc\fR) and do not
require renaming.  This script is intended for old-style address-named clips
(e.g. \fB4FED_w01.lpc\fR) extracted with the original script.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-map " FILE"
JSON rename map.  Default: \fBtmp/cat-310dx_rename_map.json\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-dir " DIR"
Directory containing clips to rename.  Default: \fBcat-310dx_lpc_clips\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-apply
Actually rename files.  Without this flag the script only prints what it
would do.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-wav
Skip \fB.wav\fR files; rename \fB.lpc\fR files only.
.TP
.B \-q
Suppress per-file output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Preview renames without making changes:
.B python3 cat-310dx_rename_clips.py
.TP
Apply renames:
.B python3 cat-310dx_rename_clips.py \-\-apply
.TP
Rename LPC files only, apply immediately:
.B python3 cat-310dx_rename_clips.py \-\-apply \-\-no\-wav
.TP
Use a custom map and directory:
.B python3 cat-310dx_rename_clips.py \-\-map my_map.json \-\-dir clips/ \-\-apply
.SH WORKFLOW
.RS
.nf
# 1. Produce rename map
python3 cat-310dx_correlate.py

# 2. Preview
python3 cat-310dx_rename_clips.py

# 3. Apply
python3 cat-310dx_rename_clips.py \-\-apply
.fi
.RE
